as described by Fitts’ law emerges even without the presence of motor noise, which is commonly believed to underlie the speed-accuracy tradeoff. This suggests an alternative theory based on suboptimal control solutions. The crux of this theory is that some features of human movement are attributable to planning variability rather than execution noise.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
